WEBVTT

02:10.125 --> 02:11.083
Nice to see you.

02:14.708 --> 02:15.666
Come on!

02:16.958 --> 02:18.833
-Hey, Monica!
-Viljar!

02:23.166 --> 02:24.083
Thank you.

02:27.291 --> 02:28.125
Hi.

02:28.583 --> 02:30.750
-Viljar Hanssen?
-Alex?

03:35.708 --> 03:36.541
Viljar!

03:37.000 --> 03:38.250
-Hey.
-Hey!

03:38.333 --> 03:40.666
-We saved a spot for you.
-Perfect.

03:41.166 --> 03:43.125
-Good to see you, man.
-Good to see you.

03:44.875 --> 03:46.000
The crew is gathered.

03:46.083 --> 03:47.583
Long time.

03:47.666 --> 03:49.333
-Hey, how are you doing?
-All right.

03:52.000 --> 03:54.208
You actually brought a sleeping bag
this time?

03:54.291 --> 03:56.291
Yeah, my parents packed.

03:57.250 --> 04:00.041
Hey, this is painful to look at.

04:31.625 --> 04:35.416
So, on Saturday you'll be going
to the AUF summer camp at Utøya.

04:35.750 --> 04:39.416
Here's the schedule, and attached
is also a draft of your speech.

04:39.500 --> 04:43.250
I started with your connection to
the island, how it inspired your activism,

04:43.791 --> 04:46.250
and then you kind of push on
to the issues.

04:46.666 --> 04:48.833
Good. I think it needs to be
a bit more personal,

04:48.916 --> 04:51.000
more about my memories from the island.

04:51.666 --> 04:54.416
And then I want to address
the challenge of youth unemployment.

04:54.500 --> 04:56.833
-I think that's very important.
-Yeah, that's good.

04:56.916 --> 04:59.458
Make sure we build in proper time
to really meet with the kids.

04:59.541 --> 05:00.375
OK.

05:00.875 --> 05:01.875
Two hours, maybe?

05:02.083 --> 05:04.375
And the committee papers
are in the briefcase.

05:04.458 --> 05:06.458
You should read those before Monday.

05:06.541 --> 05:09.416
Got it. Well, I think we're all set.
Thank you.

05:09.791 --> 05:11.000
-Get some rest.
-You too.

05:11.083 --> 05:12.083
You too, sir.

05:12.750 --> 05:13.916
-Thank you.
-Night.

05:14.000 --> 05:17.166
And tomorrow morning you have
the national security briefing at 10:00,

05:17.250 --> 05:18.083
for an hour.

05:18.166 --> 05:19.791
-I'll do it in the residency.
-OK.

05:19.875 --> 05:21.958
And bring the Justice Minister in earlier.

05:22.041 --> 05:23.666
-Yes, of course.
-Have a good night.

05:23.750 --> 05:25.625
-Good luck with the speech, sir.
-Thank you.

05:27.041 --> 05:28.041
Good night, sir.

05:28.458 --> 05:30.000
See you back here after lunch.

07:19.291 --> 07:20.291
Anders?

08:01.291 --> 08:02.791
Good morning. Welcome.

08:03.708 --> 08:05.583
-Nice to see you! Hi!
-Hey, you.

08:06.583 --> 08:07.791
Just come on in.

08:08.458 --> 08:09.958
There's seats for everyone.

08:13.083 --> 08:15.083
-This OK?
-Yeah, fine.

08:18.208 --> 08:20.083
OK. Welcome, everyone.

08:22.000 --> 08:25.333
So, welcome to the first seminar
for today.

08:25.916 --> 08:27.750
We are going to do an exercise,

08:27.916 --> 08:30.541
which I'll call
"If I Were Prime Minister."

08:31.750 --> 08:34.500
One of the good things about Utøya
is that you can meet friends

08:34.583 --> 08:37.750
and you can play music,
and maybe stay up a bit late.

08:38.291 --> 08:39.166
Yeah?

08:39.833 --> 08:44.041
But it's also an opportunity
to think about your future.

08:44.458 --> 08:46.916
You grow up so fast,
then one day it will be you

08:47.000 --> 08:49.333
that will be the leader
of your community.

08:50.000 --> 08:51.500
Viljar, can you start?

08:51.666 --> 08:53.125
Yeah, sure.

09:03.208 --> 09:04.291
Hi.

09:05.500 --> 09:06.458
How are you?

09:06.958 --> 09:08.291
So, let's see.

09:10.291 --> 09:11.125
OK.

09:13.333 --> 09:16.583
So, in Svalbard, where I come from,

09:18.375 --> 09:21.750
everyone is welcome,
regardless of nationality.

09:22.541 --> 09:24.625
We've got Norwegians,

09:25.083 --> 09:26.416
Russians,

09:26.958 --> 09:29.291
Chinese, Croatians,

09:30.333 --> 09:32.458
all living and working together.

09:32.541 --> 09:36.416
And we worked really hard
to integrate everyone.

09:36.541 --> 09:39.875
But in Svalbard, it's, like, 2,000 people.

09:41.000 --> 09:43.500
How do you translate that
to the rest of Europe?

09:44.125 --> 09:47.000
It's the principle,
and that's what's important.

09:48.583 --> 09:52.833
And if I was Prime Minister,
that's what I'd stand for.

10:27.666 --> 10:31.541
...groundwater reserves are drying up.
Sustained drought is becoming the norm...

11:47.958 --> 11:51.625
We got a white van parked out back.
Is it one of ours?

12:47.750 --> 12:51.125
OK. I'll just check the license plate
and try to find the driver.

12:59.791 --> 13:02.416
Central, will you check
a serial number for me, please?

13:26.083 --> 13:28.291
Get him out of here! Come on! Move!

13:48.791 --> 13:50.166
Prime Minister secure.

14:08.375 --> 14:09.416
We need help.

14:17.625 --> 14:20.416
We have breaking news
coming out of Oslo right now.

14:20.541 --> 14:23.333
A large explosion has gone off
in the center of the city,

14:23.791 --> 14:26.750
I think, the government district,
near the Prime Minister's office.

14:26.875 --> 14:27.791
We have no further...

14:33.291 --> 14:35.333
It isn't safe. Everybody out!

14:45.500 --> 14:46.333
Call the cabinet.

14:46.416 --> 14:49.000
I want the police director,
head of defense, and the PST.

14:49.750 --> 14:50.833
Inform the King:

14:51.500 --> 14:54.541
The Prime Minister is safe.
The government is functioning.

14:55.666 --> 14:58.291
There is a lot of debris
and smoke, but...

14:58.791 --> 15:01.625
I can clearly see a car that was flipped
onto its roof,

15:01.708 --> 15:04.500
and I'm assuming it's a result
of the blast itself.

15:06.250 --> 15:07.375
As you probably heard,

15:07.458 --> 15:10.041
there's been an explosion
in the government district in Oslo.

15:12.041 --> 15:14.666
Yeah. We don't have much information yet.

15:15.125 --> 15:17.500
Many of you have parents
who work there, OK?

15:17.583 --> 15:20.583
So you should probably call them,
if you haven't done that already.

15:21.166 --> 15:25.125
In the meantime, we'll suspend activities
until we get some more information.

15:25.208 --> 15:28.000
But for now,
you go and call your parents, OK?

15:28.958 --> 15:30.291
Any more questions?

15:32.750 --> 15:35.166
The Prime Minister?
Do you know if he's OK?

15:36.333 --> 15:37.875
-Hey, Mom?
-Hi, Viljar.

15:38.041 --> 15:39.000
Are you OK?

15:39.291 --> 15:42.333
Yeah, I'm fine. Your dad's with me.
We're at the hotel, we're fine.

15:43.041 --> 15:44.750
They say it was an explosion.

15:45.000 --> 15:47.291
Dad says there's been
some kind of explosion.

15:47.375 --> 15:49.291
-Was it a bomb?
-Yeah, we don't know.

15:50.333 --> 15:51.708
Are you both OK?

15:52.166 --> 15:54.666
Yeah, we're fine.
Torje's a bit scared, but...

15:55.125 --> 15:56.916
I'll take care of him. Yeah, I promise.

15:57.000 --> 15:59.208
We'll call you when we know
what's happened, OK?

15:59.291 --> 16:00.166
Bye.

16:01.041 --> 16:03.708
She's fine.
She said they were nowhere near.

16:03.833 --> 16:06.125
Come. Let's go. I need to change.

16:09.041 --> 16:11.041
Velna, are you OK? What's happened?

16:11.166 --> 16:13.125
Have you talked to Eric and the others?

16:13.791 --> 16:16.125
OK, cancel all the campaign meetings.

16:16.250 --> 16:19.166
Call me when you...
when you hear anything, OK?

16:19.958 --> 16:21.791
So, here's what we know so far.

16:21.875 --> 16:23.458
At around 3:30,

16:23.541 --> 16:27.166
a massive explosion was reported
in the center of the government district.

16:27.250 --> 16:30.125
Witnesses have described
extensive destruction

16:30.250 --> 16:31.750
hitting a number of buildings.

16:32.125 --> 16:35.125
There are many confirmed injured
and unfortunately also...

16:35.208 --> 16:39.625
You can see shattered windows
up to 300 yards in each...

16:39.708 --> 16:41.041
Like many countries in Europe,

16:41.125 --> 16:43.916
the Security Services have already
been operating on high alert.

16:44.000 --> 16:47.166
Counterterrorism police in Oslo have made
a number of arrests in recent months.

17:04.500 --> 17:05.541
-Hi.
-Hi.

17:05.625 --> 17:07.375
I'm Martin Nilsen, from Oslo PD.

17:07.458 --> 17:09.958
-You heard about the bomb in the city?
-Yes.

17:10.041 --> 17:11.875
I've been sent to secure the island.

17:12.416 --> 17:15.000
-Where's the ferry?
-Oh, the ferry got canceled.

17:15.791 --> 17:18.333
-Get it over here. I need it now.
-OK.

17:19.791 --> 17:21.416
-Monica?
-Go ahead.

17:21.500 --> 17:24.833
There's a policeman over here
that will need the ferry immediately.

17:25.708 --> 17:27.791
-Yeah, I will be there. OK.
-Thank you.

17:28.791 --> 17:31.291
-It will be here soon.
-OK, good.

17:41.666 --> 17:44.125
-Be there in a minute.
-It's on its way.

18:07.416 --> 18:08.250
-Hi.
-Hi.

18:08.958 --> 18:10.625
I'm Monica. I'm in charge here.

18:10.916 --> 18:12.916
Hi. Martin Nilsen, Oslo Police Department.

18:13.000 --> 18:14.041
Nice to meet you.

18:14.625 --> 18:16.875
-You heard about the explosion in Oslo?
-Yeah.

18:17.041 --> 18:19.041
-It's terrible. Is it bad?
-Yeah.

18:19.708 --> 18:22.375
The whole Prime Minister's office,
everything.

18:23.041 --> 18:25.125
-I need you to take me to the island.
-Yeah.

18:25.208 --> 18:28.500
Get everyone together, and I'll give
a debrief about the bomb.

18:28.583 --> 18:31.041
-Everyone?
-Yeah, everyone. It's important.

18:32.125 --> 18:33.416
What's in the cases?

18:33.625 --> 18:34.583
Weapons.

18:35.250 --> 18:38.000
Well, you have to cover them up.
They will scare the children.

18:38.083 --> 18:39.000
Sure.

18:40.291 --> 18:41.333
Just go ahead.

18:57.166 --> 18:59.666
-What's going on?
-Don't worry. Police have arrived.

18:59.750 --> 19:01.083
So, it's fine.

19:17.291 --> 19:18.125
Simon?

19:18.750 --> 19:20.083
-Yeah?
-Do you have my sweater?

19:22.125 --> 19:23.208
Any news on the bomb?

19:24.041 --> 19:26.250
-Here you go.
-It hit the Prime Minister's office.

19:26.333 --> 19:28.583
Yeah. And the Department of Justice.

19:28.666 --> 19:29.833
Was it Al-Qaeda?

19:30.416 --> 19:31.583
It doesn't say.

19:38.125 --> 19:38.958
Hey.

19:39.708 --> 19:40.541
Hi.

19:41.166 --> 19:43.375
This is Trond Berntsen,
our head of security.

19:43.458 --> 19:44.875
-Hi.
-Martin Nilsen, Oslo PD.

19:44.958 --> 19:47.791
They only sent one officer?
Why didn't anybody call?

19:48.041 --> 19:50.125
Everyone is needed in Oslo, it's chaos.

19:50.208 --> 19:52.125
So, they sent me to secure the island.

19:53.750 --> 19:57.291
-What precinct are you from?
-PST, Police Security Service.

19:57.625 --> 20:00.291
So you must know Jørn.
He works down at PST, doesn't he?

20:00.875 --> 20:03.416
Jørn? Yeah, sure.
He's one of my superiors.

20:04.125 --> 20:07.666
-Is everyone gathered for the debrief?
-Yes. We're calling them in now.

20:08.250 --> 20:09.666
We need to get on with this.

20:11.333 --> 20:14.083
Actually, can I see your ID?

20:15.333 --> 20:16.333
Yeah, sure.

20:20.083 --> 20:22.083
We're ready to gather in the cabin.

20:27.958 --> 20:28.791
What was that?

20:33.541 --> 20:35.250
Maybe you should go and check it out.

20:36.333 --> 20:37.750
-Use your radio.
-I will.

20:55.875 --> 20:57.250
It's probably nothing.

21:03.833 --> 21:05.500
Run! Get away!

21:06.333 --> 21:07.708
Run! Run!

21:07.916 --> 21:09.125
Over here! Come on!

21:15.166 --> 21:16.750
Run, run, Torje! Run!

21:22.333 --> 21:23.166
This way!

21:24.541 --> 21:25.416
Run, Torje!

21:25.916 --> 21:27.875
-Torje, move!
-Viljar!

21:32.375 --> 21:34.041
Simon! Simon, come!

21:40.458 --> 21:42.041
It's OK. Police.

21:43.708 --> 21:45.083
Stay away from the windows.

21:45.208 --> 21:47.666
Get down on the floor,
and I'll come inside. OK?

21:47.750 --> 21:48.958
Get down!

21:54.125 --> 21:55.291
This way!

22:09.041 --> 22:10.458
You will die today.

22:10.583 --> 22:13.708
Marxists, liberals, members of the elite.

22:16.875 --> 22:18.500
-Move!
-Quick! Down here!

22:19.333 --> 22:20.541
Down, hide here.

22:20.916 --> 22:23.125
-Down. Stay down.
-Get down.

22:24.208 --> 22:26.416
Viljar! Viljar, come on, over here!

22:27.666 --> 22:29.416
-Over here.
-The cliffs!

22:29.791 --> 22:32.166
Hang on. Simon, Simon! This way.

22:33.416 --> 22:35.041
-Come on, go!
-Run!

22:40.583 --> 22:42.458
Come on! We can make it.

22:48.291 --> 22:49.666
Come. Get down there.

22:50.250 --> 22:51.708
-Come on!
-Get down. Come.

22:53.375 --> 22:54.375
Get down.

23:07.750 --> 23:08.625
Help!

23:18.458 --> 23:22.166
-Was it a bomb?
-We don't know. Please move back.

23:22.250 --> 23:24.500
Can you please tell me
which buildings have been hit?

23:24.583 --> 23:26.958
We don't know. We just need you
to move back, please.

23:27.375 --> 23:30.166
-Come on, we're clearing the area.
-Is anyone being evacuated?

23:31.125 --> 23:32.541
-Mom.
-Viljar?

23:32.791 --> 23:34.458
-They're shooting at us.
-Viljar?

23:34.666 --> 23:35.666
Keep moving.

23:36.291 --> 23:37.125
What--

23:40.333 --> 23:42.833
I lost Viljar.
He said someone was shooting at them.

23:42.916 --> 23:44.666
-At them? Where?
-And he hung up.

23:47.541 --> 23:50.083
But he said--
What what did he say exactly?

23:50.166 --> 23:52.166
He said, "Mom, someone's shooting at us."

23:52.250 --> 23:54.375
It went really quickly.
It was just like that.

23:54.458 --> 23:55.500
-"Shooting at us"?
-Yes.

23:56.000 --> 23:57.291
It's going to voice mail.

24:08.541 --> 24:11.125
Multiple reports of gunfire
on Utøya Island.

24:11.250 --> 24:15.291
Copy that. This is O-5. We are responding.
What's the RV? Over.

24:15.958 --> 24:18.250
-Repeat, please.
-What's the RV?

24:18.666 --> 24:20.666
RV for Utøya Island, over.

24:21.458 --> 24:22.291
Stand by.

24:22.791 --> 24:23.875
Come on, come on!

24:29.750 --> 24:32.291
Sir, we may have another attack.

24:33.083 --> 24:34.833
Report of gunfire on Utøya.

24:35.916 --> 24:37.541
-What?
-No, I haven't.

24:37.625 --> 24:40.166
-The summer camp?
-Just getting details now.

24:40.708 --> 24:43.458
-What more do we know?
-We have hundreds of kids there.

24:43.541 --> 24:44.666
Any details.

24:50.291 --> 24:51.291
Where are you?

24:52.250 --> 24:53.583
Come out, you Marxists.

24:57.958 --> 25:00.666
He's coming for us. He's-- He's coming.

25:01.875 --> 25:05.041
Torje, look at me. It's going to be OK.

25:06.625 --> 25:07.541
I promise you.

25:12.250 --> 25:13.333
It'll be all right.

25:20.958 --> 25:23.291
-Get that started now!
-Get the engine started!

25:23.375 --> 25:24.750
Pull that engine!

25:24.833 --> 25:26.083
Come on!

25:27.291 --> 25:30.541
Delta Two, you take the north side.
We take the west side.

25:30.625 --> 25:32.250
-Got it? Move!
-Got it.

25:35.125 --> 25:36.416
Go, go, go.

25:41.541 --> 25:43.625
-I need an update on Delta.
-No, no.

25:44.041 --> 25:45.875
You just get them in there. I mean--

25:45.958 --> 25:47.541
This is taking too long, right?

25:47.666 --> 25:49.250
Because there is no helicopter.

25:49.625 --> 25:51.291
No, there is no helicopter at all.

25:51.583 --> 25:53.291
We just need them to be on standby...

25:53.416 --> 25:56.416
Are they on the island yet?
Where the hell are they?

25:57.708 --> 26:01.583
-...a summer camp on the island...
-Viljar, when you get this, call us.

26:01.666 --> 26:04.750
...getting confirmed reports
that there is another attack...

26:04.916 --> 26:06.250
-Nothing?
-...ongoing.

26:06.333 --> 26:09.958
This now looks like a coordinated
gun and bomb attack

26:10.041 --> 26:13.041
-on Oslo City Center and Utøya Island.
-Oh, no.

26:13.541 --> 26:15.875
I'm afraid we have no further details yet,

26:15.958 --> 26:19.166
but it looks very much
like this is by no means...

26:21.666 --> 26:22.500
Hey!

26:26.083 --> 26:27.083
It's all right.

26:31.125 --> 26:33.250
He's coming. Get down. Down.

26:35.208 --> 26:37.625
Help me! Please!

26:40.750 --> 26:42.916
Help! Somebody help!

26:49.333 --> 26:51.250
Play dead. Play dead.

27:38.333 --> 27:39.250
I can hear him.

27:40.708 --> 27:41.541
Where is he?

28:01.750 --> 28:03.833
We have to jump! Jump!

28:30.666 --> 28:32.666
Viljar! Viljar!

28:34.708 --> 28:35.708
Viljar!

28:36.166 --> 28:37.208
Viljar!

28:37.750 --> 28:39.625
-Go.
-No, no!

28:39.708 --> 28:40.666
-Viljar.
-Go.

28:43.333 --> 28:44.291
Go!

28:45.250 --> 28:46.500
You have to come with me!

28:48.875 --> 28:49.750
Viljar!

28:50.375 --> 28:51.750
-Go!
-No!

28:51.916 --> 28:52.791
Go!

28:54.666 --> 28:55.583
Go!

29:27.958 --> 29:28.791
Simon!

29:31.708 --> 29:32.750
Anders!

29:54.125 --> 29:55.500
Move, move!

29:56.416 --> 29:57.250
Shield!

29:59.583 --> 30:00.791
Move, move.

30:00.875 --> 30:01.750
-Go, go.
-Get down.

30:01.833 --> 30:03.625
Get down! Get down!

30:04.125 --> 30:06.916
Get down. Down, down. Stay hidden!

30:17.291 --> 30:18.291
It's a roadblock.

30:24.500 --> 30:27.166
-Please, you can't go down there.
-No! You don't understand.

30:27.250 --> 30:29.416
-We can hear the shoot--
-The police are--

30:32.916 --> 30:35.750
I need to get down there.
Our children are on the island!

30:35.833 --> 30:37.916
I understand, but it's too dangerous.

30:38.166 --> 30:39.583
Move farther back, please.

31:09.041 --> 31:11.583
Arms out to the side! Come forward!

31:12.250 --> 31:13.375
Come forward! Stop!

31:13.875 --> 31:15.125
Down on your knees!

31:15.833 --> 31:18.041
On your stomach! Go, go!

31:18.541 --> 31:20.083
Arms up! Cuff him!

31:20.458 --> 31:22.125
Look away. Look away from him.

31:26.958 --> 31:28.083
Down over there!

32:15.250 --> 32:18.416
On three. One, two, and three.

32:18.791 --> 32:21.250
We have a young male
with multiple gunshot wounds.

32:21.333 --> 32:23.625
No known history. Unconscious on arrival.

32:23.708 --> 32:25.375
Blood pressure's dropping. Sixty-thirty.

32:26.125 --> 32:27.625
We have to transfuse him.

32:27.791 --> 32:29.250
O-minus. Six units.

32:29.625 --> 32:33.125
There is an injury to his left shoulder.
It's a penetrating injury.

32:33.208 --> 32:34.833
We've got cardiac arrest.
We're losing him.

32:34.916 --> 32:36.416
Starting chest compressions.

32:37.250 --> 32:39.333
-We're losing him.
-Put the patch on.

32:39.625 --> 32:41.166
-Patch is on.
-150.

32:41.250 --> 32:44.166
-Charge, 150.
-150, repeat. Charging.

32:44.250 --> 32:45.291
OK, clear!

32:46.708 --> 32:48.875
-Still V-fib.
-Come on!

32:48.958 --> 32:50.958
-Thorax stable.
-We're getting a pulse.

32:51.041 --> 32:52.291
-I got a pulse.
-OK, good.

32:52.375 --> 32:54.791
Got pulse on the radial. Let's continue.

32:54.916 --> 32:57.625
There's a gunshot wound here
to his lower extremity on the right side.

32:57.708 --> 32:58.916
Could be arterial bleeding.

32:59.041 --> 33:01.166
And there's another here to his right arm.

33:01.250 --> 33:03.666
-We're losing him again.
-V-fib! Starting compressions again.

33:03.916 --> 33:06.250
-Go for 200.
-200, charging.

33:06.333 --> 33:07.333
OK, clear.

33:11.333 --> 33:13.500
Got sinus resp and a pulse.

33:13.916 --> 33:15.083
Got pulse on the radial.

33:15.166 --> 33:17.250
There is an entry wound here
to his right orbital.

33:18.333 --> 33:19.875
Exit wound here on the posterior.

33:20.208 --> 33:21.666
Blood pressure is stable.

33:21.750 --> 33:22.958
Eighty over forty.

33:23.166 --> 33:25.125
-Do we have the bleeding under control?
-Yes.

33:25.208 --> 33:27.875
-Hydrolin is in.
-OK, we have to go for surgery.

33:53.000 --> 33:54.416
All right, you can stand up.

34:02.791 --> 34:03.750
Open your mouth.

34:09.416 --> 34:12.875
I'm the duty detective, formally here
in the First Police District.

34:13.375 --> 34:16.333
-Who are you?
-My name is Anders Behring Breivik.

34:16.958 --> 34:19.500
This is a military operation,
a coup d'état.

34:20.250 --> 34:22.125
The bomb has removed the government,

34:22.208 --> 34:24.833
and here I have liquidated
a political camp.

34:25.625 --> 34:26.625
Did anyone help you?

34:27.208 --> 34:28.875
I was selected for this mission.

34:29.375 --> 34:33.541
Now my brothers are waiting for my signal
to begin the third attack.

34:33.625 --> 34:35.541
You're telling me
there's another attack planned.

34:35.625 --> 34:36.625
-Oh, yes.
-Where?

34:37.000 --> 34:40.500
I can't go into details,
but I'm authorized to negotiate.

34:41.916 --> 34:45.208
-What do you want?
-A complete ban on immigration.

34:45.958 --> 34:48.958
An end to enforced multiculturalism.

34:50.625 --> 34:54.791
And if the Prime Minister is still alive,
you should tell him if he fails to agree,

34:55.833 --> 34:57.375
the attacks will continue.

35:02.041 --> 35:04.916
Sir, Hønefoss Police
want to know what to do.

35:09.041 --> 35:11.833
-Keep him talking and bring him to Oslo.
-Understood.

35:39.416 --> 35:41.833
-Name?
-Anders Behring Breivik.

35:44.791 --> 35:46.250
-Arrested?
-Utøya.

35:49.416 --> 35:50.250
Lawyer?

35:50.333 --> 35:53.708
Yeah, there's a particular lawyer
that I would like to represent me.

35:53.958 --> 35:55.875
His name is Geir Lippestad.

35:59.041 --> 36:01.500
-Thanks so much, Anna, for staying.
-Of course.

36:03.458 --> 36:04.833
Do you need anything?

36:05.541 --> 36:09.458
No, thanks. Just keep the kids away
from the television.

36:11.208 --> 36:14.125
-Don't worry about that, OK?
-Thank you so much. Thank you.

36:17.500 --> 36:18.750
Hi, this is Lippestad.

36:21.583 --> 36:22.500
For me?

36:28.375 --> 36:29.250
Breivik?

36:32.000 --> 36:33.166
I never heard of him.

36:37.916 --> 36:39.000
I understand.

36:45.625 --> 36:46.541
What is it?

36:47.083 --> 36:48.458
The person they arrested.

36:49.916 --> 36:50.916
He asked for me.

36:52.791 --> 36:53.708
Why?

37:16.708 --> 37:18.208
He was right behind us.

37:35.000 --> 37:36.375
-Torje?
-Torje!

37:41.041 --> 37:41.958
It's OK.

37:43.208 --> 37:44.333
It's OK, Torje.

37:45.291 --> 37:46.291
It's OK.

37:48.625 --> 37:49.833
You're safe now.

37:50.458 --> 37:51.541
Where's Viljar?

37:52.666 --> 37:55.250
-You know where he is?
-We were on the cliffs, but...

37:55.583 --> 37:57.250
but he was shooting. We had to jump.

37:57.333 --> 37:58.791
Did Viljar jump?

38:02.750 --> 38:03.750
Was he shot?

38:07.583 --> 38:08.541
I'll go and check.

38:09.833 --> 38:10.916
Oh, my God.

38:16.958 --> 38:19.041
Can you check for Viljar Hanssen?

38:20.458 --> 38:21.666
Viljar Hanssen.

38:26.916 --> 38:28.208
Can you check, please?

38:28.791 --> 38:30.208
Viljar Hanssen.

38:37.916 --> 38:39.041
He's not here.

38:45.041 --> 38:45.916
He's not here.

38:46.625 --> 38:49.375
-What do you mean he's not here?
-He's not on any list.

38:50.125 --> 38:51.791
I'm calling the hospital now.

38:52.500 --> 38:54.458
Yes. Hello, I'm...

38:54.750 --> 38:58.166
I'm looking for my son,
Viljar Hanssen. He was on Utøya.

38:58.666 --> 39:01.375
Do you have any admissions by that name?

39:06.000 --> 39:07.916
OK. Thank you.

39:09.833 --> 39:10.708
No.

39:11.250 --> 39:12.666
He was on Utøya.

39:13.625 --> 39:16.208
Yes, do you have any admissions
by that name?

39:18.000 --> 39:19.083
OK. Thank you.

39:22.750 --> 39:24.791
Yes, hello. I'm looking for Viljar Han--

39:41.250 --> 39:42.333
Bone piece.

39:56.083 --> 39:57.291
-Hi.
-Sir.

40:28.041 --> 40:29.666
Please remove the restraints.

40:36.291 --> 40:38.666
Yes. Then just give us the room, please.

40:40.708 --> 40:42.750
Anders Behring Breivik. Nice to meet you.

40:43.166 --> 40:45.208
-Geir Lippestad.
-Thank you for coming.

40:51.000 --> 40:53.833
So, how do you know who...
who I am?

40:53.916 --> 40:55.541
I've seen your work before.

40:56.041 --> 40:57.125
Nine years ago.

40:57.500 --> 41:00.083
The Benjamin Hermansen neo-Nazi case.

41:01.958 --> 41:03.375
We met during the trial.

41:05.833 --> 41:07.291
-Did we?
-Yeah.

41:08.583 --> 41:10.666
I knew I would need a lawyer one day.

41:13.041 --> 41:14.416
Tell me, Mr. Breivik,

41:15.250 --> 41:16.541
what you've done today.

41:17.333 --> 41:18.708
I have started a war

41:19.208 --> 41:22.125
to take back control of Norway,
of the West.

41:22.708 --> 41:23.875
And defending me

41:24.750 --> 41:27.000
will be the greatest thing you'll ever do.

41:29.125 --> 41:31.500
Although it's my duty to take this case,

41:32.166 --> 41:34.875
I don't agree with what you've done today,
Mr. Breivik.

41:36.333 --> 41:37.500
They're innocent...

41:38.333 --> 41:39.166
children.

41:40.250 --> 41:41.708
They were traitors.

41:43.125 --> 41:44.666
Children of the elite.

41:45.541 --> 41:46.750
The leaders of tomorrow.

41:47.916 --> 41:49.875
My own children have been to Utøya.

41:50.583 --> 41:53.291
I'm an active member of the Labour Party.

41:56.000 --> 41:57.750
Does that make me a traitor, too?

41:59.333 --> 42:01.833
You are my lawyer. You're an exception.

42:10.666 --> 42:11.541
I'm so sorry.

42:29.833 --> 42:31.541
Anders and Simon are dead.

42:51.875 --> 42:52.708
Hello?

42:55.416 --> 42:56.250
Yes.

42:59.500 --> 43:02.416
He has a bad scar on his neck.
A fire burn.

43:07.416 --> 43:08.458
OK. Thank you.

43:09.458 --> 43:10.958
He's in the hospital.

43:11.500 --> 43:12.375
Let's go.

43:36.541 --> 43:38.750
Don't be afraid. I'm not operative.

43:58.250 --> 44:00.791
-Hello?
-Police. Open the door.

44:00.958 --> 44:01.791
Police?

44:07.083 --> 44:10.916
I'm Mina Anderson. I'm a detective
at the Homicide and Serious Crimes Unit.

44:12.041 --> 44:14.250
Do you understand
that you've been arrested in connection

44:14.333 --> 44:17.291
with the explosion in Oslo
and the shootings on Utøya Island?

44:17.500 --> 44:18.458
Yeah, of course.

44:26.041 --> 44:27.416
Did anyone help you with it?

44:28.333 --> 44:31.166
I'm just one cog in a network,
the Knights Templar,

44:31.791 --> 44:34.166
named in honor
of the Knights of the Crusade.

44:34.750 --> 44:36.583
We want Islam out of Europe.

44:37.833 --> 44:39.875
Can you give me any names?

44:41.083 --> 44:41.916
No.

44:42.666 --> 44:43.500
Of course not.

44:43.750 --> 44:46.041
-Clear.
-Go! Get this out of here!

44:46.833 --> 44:49.666
We have found your computer
at your mother's apartment.

44:49.750 --> 44:52.333
-Can you tell me what's on it?
-My manifesto.

44:53.500 --> 44:56.875
I sent it out so people
will understand what I've done.

44:59.041 --> 45:00.958
It's all there, 1,500 pages.

45:05.041 --> 45:07.291
We need to know if there are
more attacks planned.

45:07.375 --> 45:10.416
Yeah, this is a war.
Attacks can come at any moment.

45:11.000 --> 45:14.666
-But you need to agree to my demands.
-This is not a negotiation.

45:14.791 --> 45:17.208
I don't believe you're in a position
to dictate terms.

45:17.541 --> 45:19.041
Is another attack coming?

45:19.916 --> 45:20.916
Can we take a break?

45:21.000 --> 45:25.125
I've been trying to get medical attention
ever since I was arrested. I...

45:25.333 --> 45:28.208
cut it on a piece of someone's skull
when it shattered, and...

45:28.291 --> 45:31.541
this might be infected
if I don't get treatment.

45:31.625 --> 45:32.666
Yes.

45:33.416 --> 45:36.541
Can we pause the interview
whilst my client is

45:37.250 --> 45:38.500
seen by a medic?

45:44.708 --> 45:46.958
He could be bluffing, sir.
We just don't know.

45:56.125 --> 45:57.833
Tell him I'm listening to him.

45:59.750 --> 46:01.291
Tell him personally for me.

46:04.333 --> 46:05.916
I'm listening to him.

46:12.833 --> 46:13.833
Thank you.

46:21.875 --> 46:22.875
I'll tell him.

46:34.041 --> 46:36.250
The Prime Minister has seen your demands.

46:37.083 --> 46:38.458
He can't accept your terms.

46:39.291 --> 46:41.666
But he wanted me to give you a message.

46:42.833 --> 46:43.666
Really?

46:44.666 --> 46:45.500
He said that?

46:45.958 --> 46:48.416
It was a personal message
from the Prime Minister.

46:49.833 --> 46:53.083
He said he wants you to know
that he's listening to you.

46:55.833 --> 46:56.791
Is he in there?

46:57.750 --> 46:58.666
Watching us?

47:02.416 --> 47:05.166
We need to know
if there are any more attacks planned.

47:07.333 --> 47:10.833
Tell him I'm prepared
to call off the attacks, for the moment.

47:11.333 --> 47:13.208
How do we know that we can trust you?

47:15.791 --> 47:17.833
Because you're all listening to me now.

47:43.333 --> 47:45.125
OK. More of these, please.

47:45.208 --> 47:48.583
Have a seat right here, please.
The doctor will be with you shortly.

47:48.666 --> 47:50.333
-OK.
-OK.

47:51.333 --> 47:53.166
-Just sit and wait here?
-Yes.

47:53.458 --> 47:54.583
He'll be here soon.

48:17.083 --> 48:18.416
-Hi.
-Hi.

48:20.166 --> 48:22.541
I'm Dr. Tomas.
I'm the trauma neurosurgeon.

48:22.625 --> 48:23.750
Hi, Christin.

48:23.833 --> 48:26.416
I don't know how much you know, but...

48:26.541 --> 48:27.666
-Very little.
-Yeah.

48:27.750 --> 48:30.416
Viljar has sustained severe injuries.

48:30.916 --> 48:33.166
Gunshot wounds to both of his arms

48:33.458 --> 48:36.583
and to his lower extremity
on the right side.

48:37.041 --> 48:39.916
But what concerns us mostly is that

48:40.000 --> 48:43.250
one of the bullets exploded in his head.

48:44.458 --> 48:45.291
OK.

48:45.375 --> 48:48.541
So, I needed to do
emergency surgery on him.

48:48.875 --> 48:50.833
And it was a bit complex.

48:50.958 --> 48:53.958
There are several bullet fragments
close to his brain stem.

48:54.333 --> 48:55.833
What does this mean?

48:57.500 --> 48:59.250
That means if he survives,

48:59.833 --> 49:02.416
we will have to perform
another surgery, but...

49:03.000 --> 49:05.083
but his condition is critical.

49:05.958 --> 49:08.833
-Can we see him?
-Oh, yeah. Please.

49:11.958 --> 49:13.708
-You want to see him?
-Yes.

49:17.291 --> 49:18.500
So, please. 

49:34.250 --> 49:36.541
Sir? The press are waiting outside.

49:37.166 --> 49:38.000
One moment.

49:39.416 --> 49:40.958
We've got the final number.

49:41.375 --> 49:42.666
Eight dead in Oslo.

49:43.208 --> 49:44.958
Sixty-nine on Utøya.

49:49.708 --> 49:50.583
Wounded?

49:51.291 --> 49:52.541
At least 200.

49:54.833 --> 49:55.666
Thank you.

49:57.541 --> 49:59.583
We are all shocked.

50:00.750 --> 50:03.333
This was an attack on our government

50:03.833 --> 50:05.333
and on our children.

50:06.625 --> 50:09.291
We are a long way from understanding why.

50:10.250 --> 50:11.500
But what is clear

50:11.583 --> 50:15.916
is that our nation has been attacked
by someone who would see it changed.

50:17.625 --> 50:19.958
He would see our democracy
become tyranny.

50:21.000 --> 50:23.375
See our humanity fall.

50:25.625 --> 50:27.375
We must not give in to this terror.

50:29.041 --> 50:29.958
We must fight.

50:31.875 --> 50:33.625
But we must not become changed.

50:34.750 --> 50:37.208
Instead, we must strengthen our values

50:38.166 --> 50:41.375
and fight this terror with
the rule of law...

50:42.291 --> 50:44.541
not the barrel of the gun.

50:46.916 --> 50:47.750
Thank you.

50:56.250 --> 50:57.583
-Welcome.
-Thank you.

51:12.833 --> 51:16.041
I had a very happy upbringing.
I grew up in West Oslo.

51:17.250 --> 51:20.375
My parents divorced amicably
when I was very young.

51:20.458 --> 51:21.375
Sit down.

51:22.791 --> 51:25.125
I maintain a close relationship
with my mother.

51:26.750 --> 51:30.291
My half-sister and I are not very close,
but we speak occasionally.

51:31.416 --> 51:34.791
-What about your father?
-I haven't seen him since I was 16.

51:35.416 --> 51:38.833
We spoke a couple of years ago,
but there was really no time to meet.

51:38.916 --> 51:40.750
I was too focused on my career,

51:41.291 --> 51:44.000
my Internet businesses,
and he was living in France.

51:44.833 --> 51:48.333
How would you describe
your relationship with your mother?

51:48.541 --> 51:50.666
My mother had nothing to do with this.
She's not relevant.

51:51.375 --> 51:54.750
It's all about understanding what...
led you to do this.

51:57.458 --> 51:59.875
How many children do you have,
Mr. Lippestad?

52:03.250 --> 52:04.083
Five.

52:05.333 --> 52:06.416
And you love them?

52:07.708 --> 52:08.791
Yes, of course.

52:11.375 --> 52:14.791
I wanted to hit them
where it would hurt the most.

52:51.875 --> 52:56.291
So, he buys 900 kilos of fertilizer
and aluminium nitrate,

52:57.125 --> 52:59.000
and there were no red flags?

53:00.166 --> 53:02.083
Our focus has been on Islamist terror.

53:02.875 --> 53:06.666
-We know the far right is growing fast.
-We can't stop every threat.

53:07.625 --> 53:09.416
We did the best we could, sir.

53:10.916 --> 53:13.416
We all know that this is not good enough.

53:18.000 --> 53:20.291
I want to upgrade our national security.

53:21.541 --> 53:24.458
Intelligence, defense, policing.

53:26.333 --> 53:27.833
And I'm ordering a public inquiry.

53:28.750 --> 53:32.166
An inquiry into what happened
and how we responded.

53:33.791 --> 53:36.916
Something went badly wrong,
and we need to find out what.

53:38.791 --> 53:41.041
It's the only way
we will get through this.

53:44.541 --> 53:48.000
Christin asked me to call.
She's suspending the campaign.

53:49.500 --> 53:51.875
We're going to be staying here in Oslo
with Viljar.

53:52.208 --> 53:54.291
And Torje is here with us, so he...

53:55.333 --> 53:56.708
I called the school, yeah.

53:58.666 --> 54:01.166
Yeah. They're operating on him again now.

54:17.083 --> 54:18.125
Hi.

54:18.333 --> 54:21.000
Nice to see you.
I just came from the operating room.

54:21.625 --> 54:24.083
And... I'm sorry...

54:25.333 --> 54:28.000
that I don't bring better news than this,

54:28.083 --> 54:31.708
but I tried to get
the bullet fragments out,

54:31.791 --> 54:34.250
and I managed to take some of them out...

54:35.541 --> 54:36.375
but not all.

54:36.875 --> 54:38.083
I had to leave...

54:38.833 --> 54:41.666
some of them that were close
to his brain stem.

54:41.750 --> 54:44.125
It would have been too dangerous,
unfortunately.

54:44.958 --> 54:48.666
So, it's-- If he wakes up now...

54:50.958 --> 54:54.791
and he's not the same as he was...

54:55.708 --> 54:59.750
To evaluate his brain injury,
we have to wait and see if he wakes up.

55:00.125 --> 55:05.083
It's up to him now, but we are trying
to do everything to save Viljar's life.

55:08.458 --> 55:09.291
Thank you.

55:14.708 --> 55:15.666
This is...

55:16.750 --> 55:19.291
This is so wrong. This is-- This is wrong.

55:30.166 --> 55:31.916
It was a very dysfunctional family.

55:32.791 --> 55:35.791
Breivik's parents split acrimoniously
when he was very young.

55:37.833 --> 55:40.416
She wrote to social services
and asked for help.

55:41.041 --> 55:43.750
They had serious doubts about
the mother's capacity to parent.

55:44.125 --> 55:45.166
And his father?

55:45.750 --> 55:48.375
After the marriage collapsed,
his father cut him off.

55:49.500 --> 55:52.916
-And what about his half-sister?
-She emigrated to California.

55:53.250 --> 55:56.208
-He was about sixteen, I think.
-Sixteen, seventeen?

55:56.291 --> 55:57.791
-Yeah, something like that.
-OK.

55:58.541 --> 56:01.000
So, it was just him and his mother
after that.

56:02.000 --> 56:05.916
Well, he was obviously very isolated
all the way into adulthood.

56:06.125 --> 56:08.083
Not exactly the picture he painted.

56:08.166 --> 56:09.375
No, no, it's not.

56:12.541 --> 56:13.375
So...

56:14.875 --> 56:16.791
what are we talking about here?

56:19.458 --> 56:21.250
Developing insanity...

56:23.333 --> 56:24.250
as a defense?

56:25.041 --> 56:25.875
I think so.

56:26.500 --> 56:28.208
How else do we explain it?

56:33.166 --> 56:34.000
Yes.

56:48.333 --> 56:51.958
So, I've been appointed by your son
to lead his defense.

56:53.625 --> 56:57.458
Now, I know that he doesn't have
a relationship with his father,

56:57.541 --> 56:59.916
so I wanted to ask you some questions.

57:01.666 --> 57:03.625
What was Anders like as a child?

57:06.083 --> 57:08.916
He was-- He was a normal boy.

57:09.666 --> 57:12.833
Was kind and clever.

57:14.416 --> 57:15.750
He loved affection.

57:18.208 --> 57:21.833
Since his father left us,
I was a single parent.

57:23.791 --> 57:25.500
Any mental health issues?

57:26.166 --> 57:27.041
No.

57:27.833 --> 57:29.041
Was he ever violent?

57:29.666 --> 57:30.541
Never.

57:33.291 --> 57:37.166
Now, did you ever have any dealings
with social services?

57:38.125 --> 57:43.125
After his father left, I thought I needed
their help, but I didn't. He was fine.

57:48.041 --> 57:52.125
Did you have any sense recently
that Anders was...

57:52.833 --> 57:54.000
having problems?

57:54.500 --> 57:55.333
No.

57:55.791 --> 57:56.625
I...

57:57.666 --> 58:01.375
told the police that I saw
he had guns in his bedroom.

58:02.500 --> 58:06.916
But he told me he needed them
for hunting, and... I believed him.

58:10.833 --> 58:13.291
Will you consider testifying
in Anders' defense?

58:17.708 --> 58:18.708
What would I say?

58:20.250 --> 58:23.166
Just that there were problems
in his childhood.

58:23.250 --> 58:24.333
It would help him.

58:25.541 --> 58:26.541
But then...

58:27.458 --> 58:29.500
everyone will know who I am.

58:38.083 --> 58:41.416
Anders is entitled to a defense.

58:43.958 --> 58:45.500
Just like everyone else.

58:52.083 --> 58:53.041
I can't do it.

58:59.833 --> 59:01.333
Thank you for your time.

59:04.833 --> 59:05.833
He...

59:10.541 --> 59:12.750
He's kind of right, though, isn't he?

59:15.833 --> 59:17.500
The way the country's going.

59:21.750 --> 59:23.416
It's not like it used to be.

59:26.583 --> 59:28.166
These are difficult times.

59:34.250 --> 59:37.083
His situation is still quite critical.

59:39.041 --> 59:43.500
He's still asleep,
but we are fighting an infection.

59:45.333 --> 59:47.916
-I will be around.
-Yeah, thank you so much.

1:00:01.041 --> 1:00:03.083
...and each survivor I've met

1:00:03.166 --> 1:00:06.875
is going through
the most grueling personal recovery.

1:00:07.166 --> 1:00:09.541
But they do not go through this alone.

1:00:09.833 --> 1:00:12.416
When he attacked them, he attacked us all.

1:00:12.750 --> 1:00:15.583
Here then, we'll hear shortly
about the Prime Minister's...

1:00:46.875 --> 1:00:47.708
Hello.

1:00:48.000 --> 1:00:50.833
You fucking Nazi lover.
