1:03:05.333 --> 1:03:06.375
I'm so sorry.

1:03:11.125 --> 1:03:12.208
What was her name?

1:03:12.875 --> 1:03:13.791
Bano.

1:03:15.375 --> 1:03:17.250
She'd be so happy you're alive.

1:03:22.458 --> 1:03:24.625
This is Lara. She was on the island.

1:03:25.333 --> 1:03:27.458
She wanted to know how Viljar was doing.

1:03:27.541 --> 1:03:28.583
-Hi.
-Oh, hi.

1:03:29.333 --> 1:03:30.958
-Hi. Are you OK?
-Hi.

1:03:31.291 --> 1:03:34.291
-Yeah, I'm fine.
-Do you know Viljar well?

1:03:36.333 --> 1:03:38.250
I think everyone loves Viljar.

1:03:39.250 --> 1:03:41.666
I just played against him
in a football tournament, so--

1:03:41.750 --> 1:03:42.833
-Oh, yeah?
-Yeah.

1:03:42.958 --> 1:03:44.250
Yeah, he fouled you.

1:03:47.833 --> 1:03:48.708
Yeah.

1:03:49.333 --> 1:03:50.958
But I'll leave you, so...

1:03:51.416 --> 1:03:54.666
-Maybe I can come back when he wakes up?
-Yes, please. Very kind of you.

1:03:54.750 --> 1:03:55.583
OK.

1:03:58.250 --> 1:03:59.083
Take care.

1:04:06.666 --> 1:04:09.583
My recommendation is that...

1:04:10.625 --> 1:04:12.250
you plead insanity.

1:04:13.916 --> 1:04:17.375
The Court will have you assessed
by a forensic psychiatrist.

1:04:18.416 --> 1:04:21.416
They'll give a diagnosis,
and the Court will then decide

1:04:21.500 --> 1:04:22.791
whether to accept it.

1:04:22.875 --> 1:04:26.291
If they do,
you'll go to hospital for treatment.

1:04:27.375 --> 1:04:28.875
-Not jail?
-Not jail.

1:04:34.833 --> 1:04:36.375
People will be very angry.

1:04:38.208 --> 1:04:41.208
-It's the law.
-Will I be able to address the Court?

1:04:41.541 --> 1:04:45.458
I will petition them, and you will have
the same rights as any other defendant.

1:04:48.125 --> 1:04:48.958
OK.

1:05:03.583 --> 1:05:04.625
Listen.

1:05:04.958 --> 1:05:06.166
Is he choking?

1:05:09.666 --> 1:05:11.041
He's choking.

1:05:11.375 --> 1:05:13.166
-Can't you help him?
-He's gagging.

1:05:13.250 --> 1:05:14.458
Can you call someone?

1:05:16.416 --> 1:05:18.541
Can you come to room five? Quickly.

1:05:26.833 --> 1:05:27.791
Hi.

1:05:30.541 --> 1:05:31.625
Hi. What's going on?

1:05:31.708 --> 1:05:33.666
-He's gagging.
-He's reacting to the tube.

1:05:34.583 --> 1:05:35.875
OK, that's good news.

1:05:36.083 --> 1:05:38.000
I think we should extubate him.

1:05:38.333 --> 1:05:39.583
Saturation is good.

1:05:39.916 --> 1:05:42.250
Viljar, I'm going to take this tube
out of your throat.

1:05:42.333 --> 1:05:44.208
There's going to be a slight discomfort.

1:05:44.625 --> 1:05:46.500
-Are you ready?
-We are here, Viljar.

1:05:46.625 --> 1:05:48.625
-We are here with you.
-OK, on three.

1:05:48.708 --> 1:05:50.708
One, two, three.

1:05:55.875 --> 1:05:57.041
OK, the tube's out.

1:05:58.333 --> 1:05:59.625
Viljar, do you hear me?

1:06:03.541 --> 1:06:04.791
Very good, Viljar.

1:06:05.583 --> 1:06:07.666
Can you raise your left arm?

1:06:11.500 --> 1:06:12.333
Yes.

1:06:12.416 --> 1:06:13.625
Yes, he can.

1:06:15.708 --> 1:06:16.916
Very good, Viljar.

1:06:17.416 --> 1:06:20.041
Can you move the fingers
of your right arm?

1:06:23.000 --> 1:06:24.125
Unbelievable.

1:06:24.750 --> 1:06:26.000
Where are you from?

1:06:27.625 --> 1:06:29.958
S-- Sval-- Svalbard.

1:06:50.958 --> 1:06:52.083
What happened?

1:06:53.916 --> 1:06:55.458
It was a terrorist attack.

1:06:56.333 --> 1:06:57.166
You were shot.

1:06:57.666 --> 1:06:59.541
But it's over. You're safe now.

1:07:00.916 --> 1:07:02.500
Is Torje OK?

1:07:03.375 --> 1:07:05.250
-I'm here.
-Torje's fine.

1:07:05.625 --> 1:07:07.250
He's absolutely fine, Viljar.

1:07:10.125 --> 1:07:11.916
There was so much shooting.

1:07:13.750 --> 1:07:14.833
Yes.

1:07:16.208 --> 1:07:17.208
Yes.

1:07:18.416 --> 1:07:19.625
By just one man.

1:07:21.250 --> 1:07:22.958
Some kind of right wing extremist.

1:07:24.333 --> 1:07:25.750
How many did he kill?

1:07:31.125 --> 1:07:32.458
Seventy-seven.

1:07:43.666 --> 1:07:47.125
Simon and Anders are dead, Viljar.
I'm so sorry.

1:08:10.000 --> 1:08:11.666
Simon! Simon!

1:08:15.541 --> 1:08:16.791
Viljar!

1:08:26.541 --> 1:08:27.708
-You OK?
-Yes.

1:08:49.416 --> 1:08:50.583
OK.

1:08:51.416 --> 1:08:56.041
It is clear that this is going to be
a long recovery.

1:08:56.916 --> 1:08:58.500
Two or three years.

1:08:59.833 --> 1:09:01.875
Of course there's brain damage

1:09:02.541 --> 1:09:07.875
and these bullet fragments
that are close to you brain stem,

1:09:08.958 --> 1:09:11.041
these fragments, they could shift.

1:09:11.708 --> 1:09:12.708
And...

1:09:13.291 --> 1:09:14.500
that could be fatal.

1:09:15.083 --> 1:09:16.041
So...

1:09:16.416 --> 1:09:19.125
we are going to have to take it
one day at a time.

1:09:22.250 --> 1:09:24.333
Do you have any questions for me, Viljar?

1:09:24.416 --> 1:09:28.375
Is there anything you are wondering about?
Your rehabilitation or...

1:09:29.875 --> 1:09:31.875
-No.
-You sure you don't want to ask anything?

1:09:31.958 --> 1:09:33.208
Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

1:09:44.041 --> 1:09:45.083
OK, Viljar?

1:09:45.916 --> 1:09:48.458
Can you give me a minute?

1:09:51.375 --> 1:09:52.208
Yes.

1:09:52.833 --> 1:09:53.666
Of course.

1:10:10.000 --> 1:10:12.916
Is it necessary to restrain my client?

1:10:15.625 --> 1:10:16.666
For the moment, yes.

1:10:19.833 --> 1:10:23.791
So, I imagine every psychiatrist
in the world envies you right now.

1:10:26.333 --> 1:10:27.583
Why do you say that?

1:10:28.625 --> 1:10:32.166
Because I'm the monster,
and you get to look inside my head.

1:10:34.541 --> 1:10:36.166
You think you're a monster?

1:10:36.666 --> 1:10:37.500
No.

1:10:38.583 --> 1:10:39.750
But I think you do.

1:10:40.791 --> 1:10:42.333
You can read our minds?

1:10:43.166 --> 1:10:45.416
Within 70% of accuracy.

1:10:48.333 --> 1:10:50.875
Do you know
or do you think you know?

1:10:51.750 --> 1:10:52.625
I know.

1:10:53.250 --> 1:10:54.500
And there's a difference.

1:10:55.708 --> 1:10:59.041
-You think people can read your mind?
-Sometimes.

1:10:59.916 --> 1:11:01.458
I think they try.

1:11:02.416 --> 1:11:07.083
Did you feel like that before
the attacks or... is it a new feeling?

1:11:08.375 --> 1:11:11.083
It's not new, but it got worse
when I was planning the attacks.

1:11:11.875 --> 1:11:12.875
Worse?

1:11:13.458 --> 1:11:14.625
Yeah, much worse.

1:11:19.250 --> 1:11:20.208
It's OK.

1:11:29.416 --> 1:11:31.250
Just take a deep breath now.

1:11:39.000 --> 1:11:41.875
-I'm so sorry.
-Can you give him something for the pain?

1:11:41.958 --> 1:11:43.291
-Yes, we can--
-No! No!

1:11:43.500 --> 1:11:45.500
No more morphine.

1:11:47.583 --> 1:11:49.125
We're done now. OK?

1:11:56.916 --> 1:11:57.833
Hi.

1:11:58.041 --> 1:11:59.000
Hi.

1:12:00.291 --> 1:12:01.708
What are you doing here?

1:12:02.583 --> 1:12:03.791
I live around here.

1:12:04.125 --> 1:12:06.541
Yeah, we're checking on survivors.

1:12:08.541 --> 1:12:10.666
-Can I come in?
-Yeah, sure.

1:12:25.208 --> 1:12:26.458
How are you feeling?

1:12:28.583 --> 1:12:31.125
I'm... OK.

1:12:33.625 --> 1:12:34.666
And you?

1:12:36.291 --> 1:12:37.625
Yeah, I'm fine.

1:12:39.708 --> 1:12:44.000
I was in the shower block when it started,
so I managed to run and hide.

1:12:47.833 --> 1:12:50.250
But I got separated from my sister Bano.

1:12:58.041 --> 1:12:59.958
I'm sorry about Simon and Anders, too.

1:13:04.458 --> 1:13:05.791
It's shit.

1:13:10.333 --> 1:13:12.333
How's the food here? Is it OK?

1:13:14.000 --> 1:13:16.375
It's pretty shit, too.

1:13:18.250 --> 1:13:20.000
Actually, it's really shit.

1:13:20.833 --> 1:13:23.166
If you want, I can bring you something.

1:13:23.250 --> 1:13:26.000
-Food or anything.
-No. No, I'm fine.

1:13:26.166 --> 1:13:27.791
I don't have much appetite.

1:13:29.750 --> 1:13:32.291
Do you want anything else?
Cigarettes or...

1:13:33.041 --> 1:13:33.916
I don't know.

1:13:34.250 --> 1:13:36.125
-That would have been nice.
-OK.

1:13:36.583 --> 1:13:38.041
Except I don't smoke.

1:13:49.416 --> 1:13:50.375
Does it hurt?

1:13:50.791 --> 1:13:52.250
No, it's just...

1:13:52.541 --> 1:13:54.750
I just have to be careful.

1:13:57.833 --> 1:13:58.833
Yeah.

1:13:59.750 --> 1:14:01.250
Yeah, it's going to take time.

1:14:01.791 --> 1:14:04.000
That's what everyone keeps saying.

1:14:05.916 --> 1:14:06.958
Yeah.

1:14:09.458 --> 1:14:11.375
That's what they say to me, too.

1:14:14.166 --> 1:14:15.166
I'll...

1:14:15.875 --> 1:14:17.333
leave you in peace,

1:14:17.416 --> 1:14:21.083
but if you want, I can come back
and check in on you again.

1:14:21.250 --> 1:14:22.375
Yeah.

1:14:22.958 --> 1:14:24.083
That would be nice.

1:14:26.250 --> 1:14:27.250
OK.

1:14:30.458 --> 1:14:32.125
-Take care.
-You, too.

1:14:32.541 --> 1:14:33.625
-Bye.
-Bye.

1:14:42.833 --> 1:14:44.541
So, it's only the diagnosis.

1:14:46.416 --> 1:14:50.125
It will be up to the Court
whether to accept it.

1:14:51.291 --> 1:14:52.875
And what's their decision?

1:14:56.250 --> 1:14:58.125
Paranoid schizophrenia.

1:15:02.541 --> 1:15:06.541
In the meantime, the judge
has modified the terms of your detention.

1:15:07.708 --> 1:15:10.166
You're allowed to read newspapers.

1:15:13.250 --> 1:15:16.000
And here, you got some mail.

1:15:22.333 --> 1:15:25.000
Geir, I told you they'd be angry.

1:15:43.416 --> 1:15:44.500
Fan mail.

1:15:48.250 --> 1:15:50.250
I will be allowed to speak at the trial.

1:15:50.833 --> 1:15:52.375
This hasn't been decided yet.

1:15:52.458 --> 1:15:55.625
Now, that's very important. There are
witnesses I need to cross-examine.

1:16:10.041 --> 1:16:12.375
Anders, you can't call the Prime Minister.

1:16:13.458 --> 1:16:15.083
And Norway isn't on trial.

1:16:16.041 --> 1:16:16.875
You are.

1:16:19.958 --> 1:16:21.250
Are you sure about that?

1:16:24.625 --> 1:16:27.250
Come up. Come on, come on.

1:16:27.666 --> 1:16:28.791
Very good, come up.

1:16:28.875 --> 1:16:30.458
Come up. Yes.

1:16:31.500 --> 1:16:32.666
Yeah, very good.

1:16:33.041 --> 1:16:34.666
Come on. And the right leg.

1:16:37.458 --> 1:16:38.583
Good.

1:16:38.875 --> 1:16:40.541
Very good. Come on, come on.

1:16:43.166 --> 1:16:44.208
Come on.

1:16:45.083 --> 1:16:46.333
Yes, very good.

1:16:47.041 --> 1:16:49.583
One more. Come on, come on.

1:16:51.666 --> 1:16:52.916
Come on. Yes.

1:16:54.041 --> 1:16:55.250
And breathe.

1:17:00.125 --> 1:17:02.458
-I can't do this.
-Very good, Viljar, come on.

1:17:02.541 --> 1:17:04.541
No. No, it's not.

1:17:06.250 --> 1:17:08.000
I'm not enjoying this campaign.

1:17:09.208 --> 1:17:10.458
People are angry.

1:17:11.166 --> 1:17:12.875
Well, shouldn't you be there?

1:17:13.625 --> 1:17:14.875
I'm not leaving you.

1:17:15.333 --> 1:17:17.416
So, how will that work on election night?

1:17:18.000 --> 1:17:19.166
I'll Skype.

1:17:20.250 --> 1:17:21.291
Skype?

1:17:21.958 --> 1:17:25.000
Seriously? What kind of mayor does that?

1:17:25.708 --> 1:17:27.000
A mother mayor.

1:17:30.666 --> 1:17:33.416
Maybe you could Skype with me,
if you feel up to it.

1:17:34.916 --> 1:17:36.166
Only if you win.

1:17:37.125 --> 1:17:38.041
I'll try.

1:17:44.583 --> 1:17:45.625
Take it.

1:17:46.750 --> 1:17:49.416
-I'll call them later. It's OK.
-Seriously, take it.

1:17:49.916 --> 1:17:50.958
It's important.

1:17:51.958 --> 1:17:53.500
It's a fucking election.

1:17:56.291 --> 1:17:57.208
OK.

1:18:00.041 --> 1:18:01.375
Hi, how are you?

1:18:03.666 --> 1:18:04.500
Yeah?

1:18:06.166 --> 1:18:07.041
That's nice.

1:18:07.291 --> 1:18:11.958
...seventy-seven people,
on the 22nd of July, is criminally insane.

1:18:12.083 --> 1:18:15.541
They believe Mr. Breivik,
who was responsible for the attack...

1:18:18.041 --> 1:18:22.375
...suffers from paranoid schizophrenia,
and has done so for several years.

1:18:22.708 --> 1:18:25.958
If the Court upholds these findings
in the trial,

1:18:26.041 --> 1:18:30.750
it could result in Breivik being sent
to a psychiatric hospital for treatment,

1:18:31.000 --> 1:18:32.708
avoiding any jail time.

1:18:33.041 --> 1:18:35.166
The defendant is described by...

1:18:44.750 --> 1:18:45.708
Viljar?

1:18:46.708 --> 1:18:47.958
He can't get to you.

1:18:48.833 --> 1:18:50.708
He's never going to get to you.

1:18:55.291 --> 1:18:59.333
Although the Labour Party is expected
to make small gains across the country,

1:18:59.541 --> 1:19:03.458
polls suggest that eventually power
will shift to a coalition of parties.

1:19:03.583 --> 1:19:07.000
Ms. Solberg has been accused
of wasting what some are calling

1:19:07.083 --> 1:19:11.125
a once-in-a-lifetime boom
in the national economy. Across Europe...

1:19:11.208 --> 1:19:15.833
...groups like the Progress Party
entering government for the first time,

1:19:15.916 --> 1:19:19.541
an anti-immigration movement
that used to count Anders Breivik himself

1:19:19.625 --> 1:19:20.583
amongst its members.

1:19:20.666 --> 1:19:21.750
Hi.

1:19:22.708 --> 1:19:24.583
Yeah, everyone is there. That's good.

1:19:25.583 --> 1:19:28.208
-Yeah, and you can see me?
-Yes, I can see you.

1:19:29.291 --> 1:19:30.416
OK.

1:19:31.916 --> 1:19:37.041
I just want to say that I'm really honored
to become mayor of Svalbard.

1:19:37.583 --> 1:19:40.833
And I just want to thank you
for being so understanding.

1:19:41.125 --> 1:19:44.666
As you know,
this has been a difficult time for us,

1:19:45.291 --> 1:19:47.833
but hopefully we will be home soon.

1:19:48.833 --> 1:19:52.166
So, yeah.
And Viljar wants to say something.

1:19:52.250 --> 1:19:54.333
-Hey, Viljar!
-Hi, everybody.

1:19:56.125 --> 1:19:59.041
I just wanted to say
that I'm really proud of my mom.

1:19:59.541 --> 1:20:00.916
And hopefully they...

1:20:01.375 --> 1:20:05.083
they'll let me out of this place soon,
and we'll all get home for Christmas.

1:20:05.166 --> 1:20:07.416
-Stay strong, mate.
-Get home soon, Viljar!

1:20:07.500 --> 1:20:09.916
OK. Maybe we all should say goodbye.

1:20:10.000 --> 1:20:12.000
We'll see you soon, Christin! Goodbye!

1:20:13.583 --> 1:20:14.666
Bye-bye.

1:20:15.333 --> 1:20:16.625
-See you soon.
-Bye.

1:20:16.708 --> 1:20:18.208
-Bye-bye.
-Congratulations!

1:20:33.666 --> 1:20:35.166
They're saying he's insane.

1:20:41.333 --> 1:20:42.833
Do you think he's insane?

1:20:43.458 --> 1:20:44.458
I don't know.

1:20:46.041 --> 1:20:46.916
Maybe.

1:20:48.250 --> 1:20:49.458
I saw him.

1:20:49.833 --> 1:20:52.208
He knew what he was doing. Definitely.

1:20:59.250 --> 1:21:01.791
What are you going to do
when you get out of here?

1:21:07.208 --> 1:21:09.166
I-- I can't see the future.

1:21:09.250 --> 1:21:11.833
I just can't see it. It's like I'm...

1:21:13.000 --> 1:21:14.833
out in this no-man's-land.

1:21:19.041 --> 1:21:20.375
Do you know what I mean?

1:21:22.458 --> 1:21:23.333
Yeah.

1:21:24.833 --> 1:21:26.333
But we survived, right?

1:21:29.708 --> 1:21:31.166
What does that even mean?

1:21:34.541 --> 1:21:35.791
I really don't know.

1:21:45.208 --> 1:21:47.916
How do the families feel
about Breivik's insanity plea?

1:21:48.250 --> 1:21:50.541
I can say on behalf of my client

1:21:50.833 --> 1:21:55.166
that they strongly oppose
Mr. Breivik's psychiatric diagnosis.

1:21:55.541 --> 1:21:58.791
And as the coordinating lawyer
for the families and survivors

1:21:58.875 --> 1:22:00.666
of the 22nd of July attacks,

1:22:01.208 --> 1:22:05.875
I will be petitioning the Court today
to order further assessments.

1:22:06.166 --> 1:22:10.375
We demand that Mr. Breivik faces justice

1:22:10.958 --> 1:22:13.291
and is held accountable. Thank you.

1:22:16.750 --> 1:22:17.833
Good afternoon.

1:22:20.958 --> 1:22:24.041
After careful consideration,

1:22:24.416 --> 1:22:26.750
the Court has decided to allow

1:22:27.041 --> 1:22:30.750
further psychiatric assessment
of Mr. Breivik.

1:22:32.000 --> 1:22:32.833
Your Honor,

1:22:34.208 --> 1:22:37.583
the families welcome this decision
and they thank you.

1:22:38.333 --> 1:22:42.958
We will, of course, be calling
our own psychiatric experts.

1:22:43.041 --> 1:22:44.000
Thank you.

1:22:46.250 --> 1:22:47.166
Your Honor,

1:22:47.375 --> 1:22:50.833
the Court has already had Mr. Breivik
psychiatrically examined.

1:22:51.250 --> 1:22:55.291
Allowing further assessments
has no precedent in law.

1:22:55.875 --> 1:22:58.041
-Thank you.
-Mr. Lippestad...

1:22:59.916 --> 1:23:03.125
the Court is trying to do
what's best for Norway.

1:23:05.666 --> 1:23:07.333
Of course, Your Honor. Thank you.

1:23:08.541 --> 1:23:09.500
Thank you all.

1:24:08.291 --> 1:24:10.041
Do you want me to take your jacket?

1:24:10.541 --> 1:24:12.083
Let me put the bags here.

1:24:21.500 --> 1:24:22.916
OK. Thanks.

1:25:35.291 --> 1:25:36.916
Thank you so much for coming in.

1:25:37.750 --> 1:25:39.208
This is very difficult.

1:25:40.958 --> 1:25:42.916
Some of the parents are unhappy.

1:25:43.000 --> 1:25:45.958
They-- There have been complaints,

1:25:47.041 --> 1:25:49.375
because you are defending
such a dangerous man.

1:25:50.208 --> 1:25:51.083
Meaning?

1:25:52.916 --> 1:25:55.333
They think the school might be a target.

1:25:55.416 --> 1:25:57.208
Oh, for God's sake.

1:25:57.333 --> 1:25:58.958
I know it's very unlikely,

1:25:59.333 --> 1:26:02.666
but we have to think about
what's best for everyone.

1:26:03.250 --> 1:26:04.208
So...

1:26:04.916 --> 1:26:06.625
what exactly are you saying?

1:26:07.500 --> 1:26:09.333
We wonder if you...

1:26:10.208 --> 1:26:12.166
perhaps should find another school.

1:26:17.791 --> 1:26:18.708
I'm sorry.

1:26:20.458 --> 1:26:21.416
It's OK.

1:26:29.583 --> 1:26:30.416
Hey, hey.

1:26:37.583 --> 1:26:39.833
-How are you?
-Hi, girl, how are you?

1:26:49.916 --> 1:26:50.958
Hi, Anders.

1:26:53.125 --> 1:26:54.625
I want to change my plea.

1:26:56.875 --> 1:26:58.416
-What?
-I'm not insane.

1:27:00.958 --> 1:27:02.083
I was playing a role.

1:27:03.541 --> 1:27:06.458
-What role?
-I was playing the monster in a nightmare,

1:27:06.541 --> 1:27:10.083
but I'm not a monster.
I'm a soldier in a war, doing my duty.

1:27:11.291 --> 1:27:14.375
A leader.
And a leader doesn't give away his power.

1:27:14.625 --> 1:27:16.916
I've allowed the families to take control.

1:27:17.333 --> 1:27:20.083
But this is my trial.
I decide how it ends.

1:27:20.166 --> 1:27:22.833
I have to prove
that these attacks meant something.

1:27:24.166 --> 1:27:26.125
You'll go to prison
for the rest of your life.

1:27:27.708 --> 1:27:31.083
I have to finish what I've started,
and standing up in that court...

1:27:32.958 --> 1:27:34.500
that's the third attack.

1:27:37.583 --> 1:27:38.958
That's the whole point.

1:27:42.791 --> 1:27:43.958
That's how I win.

1:27:45.625 --> 1:27:47.416
He wants to change his defense.

1:27:48.625 --> 1:27:50.041
He wants to plead guilty.

1:27:50.625 --> 1:27:53.166
Has he given any reason? I mean, why?

1:27:54.083 --> 1:27:55.541
He wants to stay in control.

1:27:56.250 --> 1:27:58.083
And he knows the consequences.

1:27:58.958 --> 1:28:02.166
He wants to stand up
and be accountable for his actions.

1:28:02.250 --> 1:28:03.916
The psychiatric assessment was clear.

1:28:04.500 --> 1:28:07.125
The prosecution are legally obliged
to stick with it.

1:28:08.916 --> 1:28:10.500
How do we get around that?

1:28:16.333 --> 1:28:18.083
OK, so we have to start again.

1:28:18.958 --> 1:28:22.375
Infer that he knew what he was doing
every step of the way.

1:28:23.166 --> 1:28:25.875
That only someone rational
could have planned and executed

1:28:25.958 --> 1:28:27.541
something this complex.

1:28:28.250 --> 1:28:30.541
And then we have
to look into the far right

1:28:30.791 --> 1:28:33.083
and find witnesses who share his beliefs,

1:28:33.416 --> 1:28:35.916
so we can show that he's not alone
in his views.

1:28:36.791 --> 1:28:38.750
And that's the only way we can do this.

1:29:05.833 --> 1:29:06.833
-Hi.
-Hi.

1:29:09.666 --> 1:29:10.875
It's good to be back.

1:29:14.666 --> 1:29:15.500
Hi.

1:29:16.041 --> 1:29:18.125
-How are you?
-Welcome.

1:29:18.208 --> 1:29:20.041
-Thank you so much.
-Glad to see you.

1:29:20.125 --> 1:29:21.458
Glad to see you, too.

1:29:21.750 --> 1:29:23.541
-How's Viljar?
-Oh, he's fine.

1:30:00.041 --> 1:30:01.166
And this...

1:30:07.041 --> 1:30:08.208
Just relax.

1:30:11.125 --> 1:30:13.375
OK. How does it feel?

1:30:15.125 --> 1:30:17.000
-I don't know.
-Does it hurt?

1:30:20.250 --> 1:30:21.875
-Does it look normal?
-Yeah.

1:30:22.458 --> 1:30:24.333
-Would you like to have a look?
-Yeah.

1:30:34.541 --> 1:30:35.708
Viljar!

1:30:37.416 --> 1:30:38.250
OK?

1:30:38.708 --> 1:30:39.833
What do you think?

1:30:40.833 --> 1:30:41.875
I don't know.

1:30:44.708 --> 1:30:45.958
Viljar, how are you?

1:30:47.500 --> 1:30:49.875
My head hurts all the time.

1:30:50.875 --> 1:30:52.333
My shoulder...

1:30:54.416 --> 1:30:55.500
I have a lot of...

1:30:56.500 --> 1:30:57.875
phantom pains.

1:30:58.333 --> 1:31:02.250
OK, phantom pains are normal
when you have a serious brain injury.

1:31:03.125 --> 1:31:06.541
The bullet fragments
are sitting deeply in your brain,

1:31:06.625 --> 1:31:08.541
close to the brain stem.

1:31:08.625 --> 1:31:10.916
If they move just the slightest bit,

1:31:11.000 --> 1:31:13.791
-it is--
-I know what the fucking dangers are.

1:31:13.875 --> 1:31:16.000
I understand that you're frustrated.

1:31:16.625 --> 1:31:18.250
But you have to be careful.

1:32:08.125 --> 1:32:09.375
Mom! Dad!

1:32:10.208 --> 1:32:11.583
He's on the snowmobile!

1:32:11.916 --> 1:32:14.416
-What?
-Viljar! He's on the snowmobile.

1:32:42.000 --> 1:32:43.000
He's there.

1:33:06.708 --> 1:33:08.250
What is he doing?

1:33:12.750 --> 1:33:14.250
What the fuck is he doing?

1:33:27.416 --> 1:33:28.666
Oh, my God.

1:33:44.375 --> 1:33:46.375
-Viljar!
-Viljar.

1:33:46.958 --> 1:33:47.916
Viljar.

1:33:49.125 --> 1:33:50.083
Go away!

1:33:51.000 --> 1:33:51.833
I'm fine.

1:33:52.791 --> 1:33:54.000
-I'm fine.
-Viljar.

1:33:55.750 --> 1:33:58.250
I can't-- I can't live like this.

1:33:59.916 --> 1:34:02.375
Pretending everything
is going to get better.

1:34:03.416 --> 1:34:04.416
It's not.

1:34:05.166 --> 1:34:07.083
It's all still here in my head.

1:34:07.541 --> 1:34:10.041
And I can't-- I can't get rid of it.

1:34:11.625 --> 1:34:13.833
-What the fuck am I supposed to do?
-Come on.

1:34:18.375 --> 1:34:19.291
Tell me!

1:34:23.875 --> 1:34:24.708
I don't know.

1:34:28.083 --> 1:34:30.208
I just wish it had been me, not you.

1:34:38.583 --> 1:34:39.416
Viljar.

1:34:53.458 --> 1:34:54.583
Let's go home, OK?

1:35:17.416 --> 1:35:18.500
My client,

1:35:19.000 --> 1:35:20.208
Anders Breivik,

1:35:20.875 --> 1:35:22.875
writes about you in his manifesto.

1:35:23.625 --> 1:35:25.250
He obviously admires you.

1:35:25.958 --> 1:35:27.708
Many people admire me.

1:35:28.166 --> 1:35:29.416
It's not because of me.

1:35:30.208 --> 1:35:34.291
It's because of the ideas I have
about what's going on in the world.

1:35:36.041 --> 1:35:37.333
Did you ever meet him?

1:35:37.625 --> 1:35:38.458
Yes.

1:35:39.416 --> 1:35:43.333
But I have to be careful
who I work with, what I do.

1:35:44.250 --> 1:35:46.416
And he's not from around here, you know.

1:35:47.250 --> 1:35:48.958
He's from your side of Oslo.

1:35:49.833 --> 1:35:52.458
But, yes, we share the same vision
of the world.

1:35:54.125 --> 1:35:55.541
He says a war is coming.

1:35:57.333 --> 1:35:59.333
I'd say the war already started.

1:36:02.291 --> 1:36:04.333
Are you a member of the Knights Templar?

1:36:04.916 --> 1:36:07.083
There's so many organizations.

1:36:07.375 --> 1:36:09.791
We are very strong
all across Scandinavia,

1:36:09.875 --> 1:36:12.375
Northern Europe,
Eastern Europe, of course.

1:36:12.833 --> 1:36:15.750
Very strong in the UK,
new groups forming all the time.

1:36:18.416 --> 1:36:19.500
How about America?

1:36:20.625 --> 1:36:21.666
Storm front.

1:36:22.250 --> 1:36:23.333
Growing fast.

1:36:23.625 --> 1:36:26.333
Very fast. Joining up with Europe.

1:36:28.833 --> 1:36:30.041
You know, Lippestad,

1:36:30.833 --> 1:36:33.416
there's a lot of fear and anger out there.

1:36:35.375 --> 1:36:39.333
And that's why tomorrow
is going to belong to us.

1:36:42.875 --> 1:36:45.041
Will you testify in my client's defense?

1:36:57.708 --> 1:36:59.666
We got an e-mail from the lawyers.

1:37:01.625 --> 1:37:04.375
There's a briefing on the mainland,
they want us to go.

1:37:06.041 --> 1:37:08.375
So we know what to expect from the trial.

1:37:15.541 --> 1:37:16.458
You should go.

1:37:21.875 --> 1:37:22.708
Sveinn.

1:37:25.750 --> 1:37:28.583
We both need to engage in this.
It's important.

1:37:30.041 --> 1:37:32.416
Engaging nearly cost our sons
their lives.

1:37:33.416 --> 1:37:34.625
They're still here.

1:37:35.250 --> 1:37:36.166
Are they?

1:37:40.000 --> 1:37:43.291
I don't care about
Anders fucking Breivik and his trial.

1:37:45.166 --> 1:37:48.708
I just want us to get on with our lives.
That's it. That's all.

1:37:53.125 --> 1:37:54.125
OK.

1:38:18.166 --> 1:38:19.000
Hi.

1:38:20.750 --> 1:38:22.333
I haven't heard from you.

1:38:23.041 --> 1:38:25.083
I was just wondering if you're OK.

1:38:26.625 --> 1:38:28.291
Call me if you want to talk.

1:38:44.541 --> 1:38:45.375
Hey.

1:38:46.833 --> 1:38:48.666
-Hey.
-You want to...

1:38:49.375 --> 1:38:50.875
watch a movie or something?

1:38:52.125 --> 1:38:55.166
Maybe later. I'm just doing some music.

1:39:14.625 --> 1:39:15.458
Torje...

1:39:18.000 --> 1:39:18.833
talk to me.

1:39:21.875 --> 1:39:22.708
I'm fine.

1:39:25.791 --> 1:39:26.750
No, you're not.

1:39:30.416 --> 1:39:31.958
You know you can talk to me.

1:39:37.541 --> 1:39:39.125
You're the one who got hurt.

1:39:40.291 --> 1:39:41.166
Not me.

1:39:45.541 --> 1:39:46.791
You were there, too.

1:39:57.125 --> 1:39:57.958
Look...

1:40:00.083 --> 1:40:02.916
I'm sorry Mom and Dad have been
looking after me so much.

1:40:07.000 --> 1:40:09.833
I know it has been... tough for you.

1:40:13.333 --> 1:40:14.458
But we're home now.

1:40:18.958 --> 1:40:19.875
Yeah.

1:40:43.041 --> 1:40:47.541
So, the Court has decided
that Breivik can speak in his own defense.

1:40:48.083 --> 1:40:48.916
Yes.

1:40:50.125 --> 1:40:51.416
I understand.

1:40:51.500 --> 1:40:54.250
How can it be right
that he's allowed to speak? How?

1:40:54.333 --> 1:40:57.625
The Court has to preserve his rights.
And he does have rights.

1:41:02.041 --> 1:41:03.791
He doesn't have any rights.

1:41:04.458 --> 1:41:08.291
You're talking about the man who killed
my son! I would hang him from a tree!

1:41:11.625 --> 1:41:12.458
No!

1:41:12.875 --> 1:41:15.791
He shouldn't be allowed to turn this trial
into propaganda.

1:41:15.916 --> 1:41:19.916
I agree and I'm going to be there
to make sure that doesn't happen.

1:41:20.000 --> 1:41:24.250
We are closing the trial
with victims' testimonies.

1:41:24.333 --> 1:41:27.333
That's why it's important
that those who survived

1:41:27.416 --> 1:41:32.041
speak about their experience
to stand up against his defense.

1:41:32.416 --> 1:41:35.708
I think it would be
a very, very strong statement.

1:41:36.083 --> 1:41:39.916
He gets to speak. My daughter's
too scared to leave her bedroom.

1:41:40.000 --> 1:41:41.541
What about my daughter's voice?

1:41:41.625 --> 1:41:44.291
They would be the voices
of those who cannot speak,

1:41:44.666 --> 1:41:46.083
because they were there.

1:41:46.791 --> 1:41:48.791
And we need to hear their stories.

1:42:03.958 --> 1:42:05.583
They've sent Viljar a letter.

1:42:07.208 --> 1:42:09.291
They want him to testify at the trial.

1:42:10.916 --> 1:42:12.375
He doesn't have to do it.

1:42:13.833 --> 1:42:16.083
We can just get the doctor to excuse him.

1:42:20.583 --> 1:42:21.875
Maybe he needs to do it.

1:42:25.208 --> 1:42:26.458
What does that mean?

1:42:29.083 --> 1:42:30.666
Maybe he needs to face it.

1:42:32.333 --> 1:42:35.291
-How do we know it won't set him back?
-We don't.

1:42:36.375 --> 1:42:37.916
It's a hell of a risk.

1:42:44.833 --> 1:42:45.958
It's his choice.

1:43:17.291 --> 1:43:18.208
Hi.

1:43:18.625 --> 1:43:19.625
Hey.

1:43:21.041 --> 1:43:22.750
I've been worried about you.

1:43:24.083 --> 1:43:25.041
I'm fine.

1:43:27.041 --> 1:43:29.375
I just received a letter.

1:43:30.541 --> 1:43:31.958
They want me to appear.

1:43:32.458 --> 1:43:33.500
At the trial.

1:43:34.250 --> 1:43:36.250
Yeah. Me, too.

1:43:37.833 --> 1:43:39.708
Do you think you can face him?

1:43:48.750 --> 1:43:49.750
Viljar!

1:43:50.375 --> 1:43:51.458
Are you still there?

1:43:52.083 --> 1:43:53.375
Yeah, I'm here.

1:43:55.458 --> 1:43:57.000
Do you think you can do it?

1:43:58.416 --> 1:43:59.250
Well...

1:43:59.750 --> 1:44:02.166
I can't even walk down the fucking street.

1:44:15.125 --> 1:44:16.000
Your Honor,

1:44:16.083 --> 1:44:19.416
on the 22nd of July, 2011,

1:44:20.166 --> 1:44:21.916
Anders Behring Breivik

1:44:22.833 --> 1:44:25.416
carried out a dual terror attack,

1:44:25.666 --> 1:44:29.166
taking the lives of 77 innocent people.

1:44:30.041 --> 1:44:34.791
Hundreds more were injured
and left forever scarred by his actions.

1:44:36.625 --> 1:44:40.250
Mr. Breivik initially entered
a plea of insanity.

1:44:41.666 --> 1:44:45.166
Now he wishes to be held accountable
for his actions,

1:44:45.791 --> 1:44:47.750
but Norwegian law is clear.

1:44:48.958 --> 1:44:50.375
If there is any doubt

1:44:50.833 --> 1:44:54.500
as to Mr. Breivik's state of mind
on the 22nd of July,

1:44:55.250 --> 1:44:56.958
we, the prosecution,

1:44:57.041 --> 1:45:02.291
have no choice but to request
the Court to find him guilty,

1:45:03.791 --> 1:45:08.375
but sentence him to
mandatory psychiatric treatment

1:45:08.708 --> 1:45:09.833
in a secure facility.

1:45:12.416 --> 1:45:13.708
We will not seek

1:45:14.500 --> 1:45:18.166
to deny the crimes committed
on July 22nd.

1:45:18.791 --> 1:45:21.416
However, we will argue
that Mr. Breivik

1:45:21.916 --> 1:45:25.375
was not psychotic during these attacks.

1:45:26.583 --> 1:45:31.125
Instead, we say he knew exactly
what he was doing.

1:45:31.916 --> 1:45:34.250
These were political acts.

1:45:38.958 --> 1:45:40.000
Mr. Breivik.

1:46:13.750 --> 1:46:16.833
Today I speak on behalf of Europeans

1:46:17.583 --> 1:46:19.458
who have been deprived

1:46:19.958 --> 1:46:23.125
of their ethnic, indigenous,

1:46:23.708 --> 1:46:26.333
cultural, and territorial rights.

1:46:28.166 --> 1:46:30.708
The prosecution tell you I'm insane.

1:46:32.250 --> 1:46:35.125
They do this because they fear me.

1:46:35.875 --> 1:46:38.708
Because I have committed
the most sophisticated,

1:46:38.958 --> 1:46:43.083
the most spectacular
political assassination in Europe

1:46:43.625 --> 1:46:45.625
since World War II.

1:46:46.541 --> 1:46:47.625
And why?

1:46:48.833 --> 1:46:50.958
Because Norway,

1:46:51.583 --> 1:46:52.583
Europe...

1:46:53.333 --> 1:46:55.208
these are not real democracies.

1:46:55.916 --> 1:46:59.375
Is it democratic for a nation
not to be consulted

1:46:59.458 --> 1:47:01.875
about whether it becomes multicultural?

1:47:02.333 --> 1:47:06.666
To force them to become a minority
in their own capital?

1:47:08.416 --> 1:47:11.958
Many will realize this
in the coming decades

1:47:12.041 --> 1:47:14.958
and pick up arms, just as I did.

1:47:15.833 --> 1:47:17.958
The defendant has said enough, Your Honor.

1:47:18.041 --> 1:47:19.833
You must hurry up, Mr. Breivik.

1:47:19.916 --> 1:47:21.708
I must be allowed to finish my statement.

1:47:21.791 --> 1:47:23.875
This is very upsetting for the families.

1:47:24.000 --> 1:47:27.708
Your Honor, the defendant must be allowed
to finish his statement. Thank you.

1:47:28.833 --> 1:47:31.125
You may continue, Mr. Breivik.

1:47:32.833 --> 1:47:36.333
When peaceful revolution
is made impossible,

1:47:37.208 --> 1:47:41.166
then violent revolution
is the only option.

1:47:42.291 --> 1:47:46.750
I demand to be acquitted
because I acted in defense of my country.

1:47:53.791 --> 1:47:55.125
I got eight weeks.

1:47:58.166 --> 1:47:59.708
I want to walk unassisted.

1:48:00.750 --> 1:48:04.041
No stick, no shaking, no breathlessness.

1:48:05.916 --> 1:48:07.875
You're still very weak.

1:48:09.750 --> 1:48:12.041
Just tell me what I need to do.

1:48:16.291 --> 1:48:18.416
Thank you for coming today,
Prime Minister.

1:48:18.958 --> 1:48:22.583
I want to begin to explore to what extent
government was aware

1:48:22.958 --> 1:48:25.333
of the threat posed
by Anders Behring Breivik

1:48:25.416 --> 1:48:27.708
prior to his attacks on the 22nd of July.

1:48:27.833 --> 1:48:30.083
That was obviously a question
that concerned me greatly.

1:48:30.625 --> 1:48:33.333
The Security Services told me
they had no warnings,

1:48:33.500 --> 1:48:35.833
that he operated completely out of sight.

1:48:36.208 --> 1:48:39.750
Prime Minister, our investigation
suggests something different.

1:48:42.250 --> 1:48:46.083
We have discovered
that Mr. Breivik's purchase of chemicals

1:48:46.166 --> 1:48:48.208
that he used in the construction
of the bomb

1:48:48.625 --> 1:48:53.416
came to the attention
