1:56:03.541 --> 1:56:04.958
She won't do it, either.

1:56:07.625 --> 1:56:08.625
Pathetic.

1:56:10.375 --> 1:56:13.750
You know there's not once
when I could rely on her?

1:56:15.125 --> 1:56:16.916
-Not even once.
-Anders...

1:56:18.500 --> 1:56:23.416
there isn't one single person
who will agree to defend your actions.

1:56:25.916 --> 1:56:27.291
I don't need anyone.

1:57:30.083 --> 1:57:31.250
We were refugees.

1:57:33.166 --> 1:57:34.666
We were running from war.

1:57:37.333 --> 1:57:40.041
It took a very long time
for Norway to feel like home.

1:57:42.750 --> 1:57:45.333
And some people
were really suspicious of us.

1:57:46.250 --> 1:57:48.875
They were angry that we were even here.

1:57:50.416 --> 1:57:53.000
But my sister Bano, she really helped me.

1:57:54.000 --> 1:57:55.541
She told me that Norway...

1:57:56.750 --> 1:57:57.916
Norway's great.

1:58:00.166 --> 1:58:02.416
It could mean security

1:58:03.041 --> 1:58:03.916
for us.

1:58:05.250 --> 1:58:06.083
And freedom.

1:58:07.291 --> 1:58:08.125
And hope.

1:58:11.958 --> 1:58:15.958
And that's exactly what I felt
around the campfire at Utøya...

1:58:17.250 --> 1:58:18.500
the night before.

1:58:22.000 --> 1:58:23.125
But the next day,

1:58:23.958 --> 1:58:25.541
when we were attacked and...

1:58:28.125 --> 1:58:29.583
